        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-01 14:41:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Hmm - do we have actors with duplicate name? APPC and APPCLCM were\n>  > declared different right?\n> \n> Currently, they're both \"APPC\" - I didn't change that.  AFAIK, the latter is no longer used, so it gets ignored.  Nothing has been done to upgrade APPC-LCM.  However, if we want to support both, we can certainly name them differently.\n\nThat's interesting. The APPC is ONAP-only, using a mucked up modifyConfig from OpenECOMP days. At some point we want to migrate to APPC-LCM (the name that should have I thought), which is what AT&T uses internally for real. And what ONAP should migrate to.\n\nPerhaps we rename APPC with the old ModifyConfig to APPC-Legacy in order to differentiate it from the APPC LCM that we should use in the future.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
